### The Honest Differentiator

There are many consultants who serve higher education. Most of them are former administrators who hung out a shingle after retirement. They are smart people with good intentions.

But they share a common limitation: They work from the outside in.

They schedule meetings. They request documents. They conduct interviews. They build understanding slowly, billing by the hour, constrained by what you choose to share with them.

